pr_description:
This enables displaying notifications based on socket status. 
this updated the state object in the app; as well as some socket handlers.

Eventually I think it might bet worth abstracting the socket updates to a function so we don't have a ton of functions like 

```
  handleDisconnected = () => {
    this.setState({
      network: "disconnected"
    });
  };
```

but it's not a big deal

GET INTO IT!

At first when I got on this issue I was like:

![stubborn-shiba](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12987958/28251616-58fc1296-6a4f-11e7-9e04-93b0defb176b.png)


but now i'm like

![devj58mxoaai9x5](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12987958/28251618-5c617516-6a4f-11e7-8498-1ffb84677a84.jpg)


## UI UPDATES! 

![jul-16-2017 17-48-19](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12987958/28251615-535a9b8c-6a4f-11e7-8cae-3a24ce028037.gif)

